The WOOL software libraries support the concept of a "variable store", a simple list of variables that can be used to store the state of your application.

[[Variables8]]
===
title: Variables8
tags: 
speaker: Bob
colorID: 0
position: 2971,72
---
For example, many of your dialogues might use a variable called "userName" that is set after account creation. So you can say things like "Hey $userName!".

[[Variables9]]
